{"type":"message","id":"77ef8060","parentId":"ea045227","timestamp":"2026-04-27T18:04:52.514Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the results:\n\n**Gmail:** 1 new email from PetScreening - \"Your profile is incomplete\" - this is likely IMPORTANT (service notification/category update), not urgent bills/payments/security alert. Let me read it to confirm.\n\n**iCloud:** 3 emails, but all appear to be READ already (R flag). The \"!\" flag likely means unread. Let me check - the output shows:\n- ID 8: \"!\" and \"R\" - unread and read? Or unread?\n- ID 7: \"R\" - read\n- ID 6: \"R\" - read\n\nWait, let me re-read the himalaya output. The FLAGS column shows:\n\n\n- 8: \"! R\" - might mean unread (exclamation) and then R might mean something else\n- 7: \"R\" - read\n- 6: \"R\" - read\n\nActually, in himalaya, the flags typically are:\n- \"!\" = flagged/important\n- \"R\" = read\n- \"D\" = deleted\n\nSo ID 8 has \"!\" and \"R\" which would mean it's flagged but also marked as read? That's confusing. Or maybe \"!\" means unread and \"R\" means something else. Let me think about standard email flags...\n\nActually in standard IMAP:\n- \\Seen = read (R)\n- \\Flagged = flagged (!)\n- \\Answered = answered (A)\n- \\Deleted = deleted (D)\n- \\Draft = draft (D)\n\nSo ID 8 with \"!\" and \"R\" would mean flagged and read. That's odd.\n\nHmm, but maybe the himalaya output format is different. Let me just read the emails to be sure.\n\nFor Gmail, let me read that email to get more context.\n","thinkingSignature":"2dcdc2ce12c5800b52c2013457a49ce9c875080164cdc42dec6776d4e9ac5568"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uf5rqo18izh9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail read 19dd01c4e4c68577 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uf5rqo18izh9_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya message read 8 --account icloud 2>&1 | head -40","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":367,"output":485,"cacheRead":19584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777313077952,"responseId":"063ed836949c9e76fee1671437e71707"}}
